#. <section class="sutta" id="sn13.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn13.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 13"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 13"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Abhisamayavagga"
msgstr "1. Comprehension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn13.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Sambhejjaudakasutta"
msgstr "3. Where the Waters Flow Together"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn13.3:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn13.3:1.2"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge."

msgctxt "sn13.3:1.3"
msgid "gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, tato puriso dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni uddhareyya."
msgstr "Suppose a person was to draw two or three drops of water from such a place."

msgctxt "sn13.3:1.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn13.3:1.5"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni yaṃ vā sambhejjaudakan”ti?"
msgstr "Which is more: the two or three drops drawn out or the water in the confluence?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn13.3:2.1"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ sambhejjaudakaṃ;"
msgstr "“Sir, the water in the confluence is certainly more."

msgctxt "sn13.3:2.2"
msgid "appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni."
msgstr "The two or three drops drawn out are tiny."

msgctxt "sn13.3:2.3"
msgid "Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sambhejjaudakaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatānī”ti."
msgstr "Compared to the water in the confluence, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn13.3:2.4"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …"
msgstr "“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”"

msgctxt "sn13.3:2.5"
msgid "dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn13.3:2.6"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
